            . I am in Mr. Hudson's employ, he is a <rs id="t18100919-131-viclabel753" type="occupation">pewterer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18100919-131-victim1066 t18100919-131-viclabel753"></join> in <placeName id="t18100919-131-crimeloc754">Fetter-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18100919-131-crimeloc754" type="placeName" value="Fetter-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18100919-131-crimeloc754" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18100919-131-off751 t18100919-131-crimeloc754"></join>. On the 28th of July I marked three pieces of pewter, in the morning; the prisoner, after seven o'clock, was paid his wages; he went away; one piece of marked pewter was missing, the prisoner was brought back to the premises, I was present when he pulled it out of his pocket himself. This is the pewter, I marked it with the initials of my own name; it is Mr. Hudson's property.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. At times I am not so well in my recollection as I ought to be; four years ago I was taken with the brain fever, I was in St. Martin's workhouse, out of my mind. I did not know I had any thing about me until I came into the accompting house, and when he said he would search me, I put my hand into my breeches pocket and took it out.</p>
               <p>
